Male. No signfiicant microanatomic lesions observed.
Male. An aggregation of P. neurophilia spores is observed in the spinal cord. M. streisingeri are observed in mesonephric duct. Sections of the spinal cord are absent others run at different angles suggesting a possible spinal deformity.
Male. Aggregations of P. neurophilia are observed in the brain and spinal cord.
Male. Multiple aggregations of P. neurophilia are obaserved in the spinal cord and multiple ventral nerve roots along with multi focal inflammation in the meninx. There is a large focus of granulomatous inflammation at the swim bladder bifurcation and 2 smaller granulomas in the caudal coelom. Acid fast pending. P. neurophilia observed in CNS and in granulomas.
Female. No signfiicant microanatomic lesions observed.
Female. Liver / /Liver exhibits extenisve nuclear and cellular pleomorphisms. Multiple areas exhibit hypertrophy an vaculoation of hepatocytes whereas other regions exhibit increased eosinophila. Consistent with toxicopathic changes but quite unusual. A clear distinction between these variable regions is not evident and hence diagnosis as hepatocellular carcinoma was not confirmed. / /SEAN: There are definitely a bunch of clusters of pigment laden macrophages (probably hemosiderin) throughout the liver. There are also multifocal clusters of disorganized almost nodular swollen hepatocytes with either clear vacuolated cytoplasm or hypereosinophilic cytoplasm. If this were a mouse they would probably be described as pre neoplastic foci. Toxicant exposure is a differential here particularly if it s a carcinogen. I can t say I ve seen anything similar in a zebrafish but my gut says these are probably preneoplastic lesions.

Female/ /The fish is severely emaciated. Intestinal folds are diffusely severely blunted and epithelial cells are diffusely severely attenuated. The small intestine contains dozens of worms threaded through the mucosa consistent with Pseudocapillaria tomentosa. The lamina propria contains an inflammatory infiltrate composed of granulocytes macrophages lymphocytes and rodlet cells. There is widespread lymphohistiocytic myositis and muscle loss with intracellular clusters of spores consistent with Pseudoloma neurophilia. Ova are arrested at previtellogenic stages. / /Enteritis secondary to P. tomentosa infection / /Myositis secondary to P. neurophilia infection/ /Emaciation/ /
Female/ /The fish is severely emaciated. Intestinal folds are diffusely severely blunted and epithelial cells are diffusely severely attenuated. The small intestine contains dozens of worms threaded through the mucosa consistent with Pseudocapillaria tomentosa. The lamina propria contains an inflammatory infiltrate composed of granulocytes macrophages lymphocytes and rodlet cells. Ova are arrested at previtellogenic stages. The mesonephric duct contains abundant myxidium. The gill epithelium is diffusely plump and reactive. / /Enteritis secondary to P. tomentosa infection / /Emaciation / /
Female/ /Gill epithelial cells are multifocally plump and reactive. / /Reactive gill epithelium.
Male/ /Gill epithelial cells are multifocally plump and reactive. / /
Male/ /The animal is severely emaciated with muscles in various stages of atrophy and degeneration. Hepatocytes are diffusely atrophic. The intestinal folds are severely blunted and lined by attenuated low cuboidal epithelium that is moderately dysplastic. Goblet cells are absent. The lamina propria contains moderate numbers of lymphocytes and macrophages. Gill epithelial cells are diffusely plump and reactive. / /Severe atrophic enteritis with generalized emaciation. / /While no cause of emaciation can be immediately identified in sections examined the likely cause is the entity that resulted in the severe atrophic enteritis. This could have been a single event and the lesions observed might be due to an attempt at regeneration of the intestinal epithelium. / /Differentials include P. tomentosa infection or the presence of an intestinal neoplasm out of the plane of section. / /

CaseDescr_right: 10 moribund zebrafish were submitted for histopathology.

Male. The intestine is extremely dilated with debris and occasional brine shrimip cysts. One renal tubule is dilated with debris consistent with nephrocalcinosis.

Male. Testicular hypertrophy with mature spermatids filling over 3 4 of the coelomic cavity. Focally extensive epidermal hyperplasia and sloughing on the ventral jaw.
Female. Jaw deformity. There is a mat of fungal hyphae in the cranial lobe of the swim bladder. Fungal aerocystitis. Hepatic megalocytosis in a locally extensive area of liver.
Male. epidermal hyperplasia and sloughing ventral and dorsal head. Multiple small thyroid follicles with colloid in the ventral jaw. Tip of operculum is everted.
Male. Lower jaw extends past upper jaw with cartilage proliferation at the tip.
Male. Multiple renal tubules are profoundly dilated with basophilic cebris consistent with nephrocalcinosis. Myodegernation in the head.
Male. Mild diffuse gill epithelial hypertrophy and hyperplasia.
Female. There are only immature eggs in the ovary. Diffuse mild myodegeneration. Mild to moderate gill epithelial hypertrophy. Increased nucleus to cytoplasm ratio in hepatocytes.

Histopathology:
Female. Ovary: numerous small pigmented atritic eggs amongst more normal ovarian tissues (i.e. some vitologenic eggs are present). Intestine: similar to Fish 2 Moderate Focal chronic enteritis with lesion extending into coelom as posterior intestine. Curvature of spine kyphosis was evident but individual vertebrae appeared normal.
Female. Profound diffuse edematous changes in debris and extending into scale pockets. Consistent with dropsy. These extensive bubble like structures could also be a result of gas supersaturation. One granulomatous lesions somewhat consistent with mycobacteriosis in roof of mouth. Acid fast negative.
Male. Intestine: severe focal chronic enteritis at distal aspect of intestine near anus. Lesion extends from lamina propria into coelom. Overlying epithelium appears normal
Male. Curvature of spine as in Fish 3 kyphosis was evident but individual vertebrae appeared normal.

Female. NSL / /F3 has similar spinal changes to F1
Male. Somatic muscle. 2 regions of moderate chronic myositis with hylanine appearance. / /Multifocally skeletal muscles lack striation and the sarcoplasm is replaced by dense non striated brightly eosinophilic acellular material that is similar in appearance to collagen although there is no evidence of muscle atrophy or tissue placement by fibrosis. Rather myocytes themselves appear to have changed and become full of dense proteinaceous material. This material is occasionally ossified.
Female. Intestine. Moderate post mortem autolysis but tissues were still adequate for interpretation. CNS: One region of chronic gliosis in the anterior ventral spinal cord at the junction with the hind brain. Sean Luna / /Multifocally there are incomplete divisions between vertebral bodies with up to three vertebrae connected by a common lumen that contains varying amounts of notochord remnant. Multifocally there are degenerative changes in the notochord remnants with proliferation of primitive physaliferous cells. These cells are small with open faced nuclei and a moderate amount of vacuolated lightly granular cytoplasm. Most of the time these proliferative cells are associated with distorted central vertebral bodies that are variably mineralized. Rather than being filled with notochord remnant connected vertebral bodies occasionally have centralized strands of densely packed presumably collagenous material that frequenly contain proliferative cells and bridges the dorsal and ventral aspects of the vertebral bodies. There is frequent deformation of the bony portions of vertebral bodies with rests of proliferative cells surrounded by bone.

Male. Gill severe diffuse chronic epithelial hyperplasia extending to epithelium of gill chamber. / /Along with the gill hyperplasia this fish has vertebral changes similar to F1.

CaseDescr_left: Six fish with early pie slice lesions were submitted for bacteriology and histopathology.
CaseDescr_right: Six fish with early pie slice lesions were submitted for bacteriology and histopathology.
Histopathology:
Male. Around the pancreas and distal gut there are numerous rodlet cells. Proliferative areas of the lamina propria extend through serosa to the ventral body wall in the distal gut (cross section S7). No body wall lesion is detected in sections examined.
Male. Chronic inflammation with granulomas surrounds the swim bladder and extends around the testis and distal intestine. Ventral scale pocket edema. There is a dermis lined invagination at the caudal end of the coelom extending up to the caudal swim bladder. Multi focal areas of mild proliferation in the intestinal lamina propria. Acid fast bacilli are observed within granulomas consistent with mycobacteriosis. (Sagittal sections)
Male. There is duct hyperplasia and inflammation in the pancreas (cross section S4). Locally extensive proliferation in the lamina propria through serosa into ventral body wall through vent. Inflammation extends up the caudal coelom. No lateral body wall lesion is detected in sections examined. Acid fast negative.
Male. Eosinophilic round cell accumulation in the area of the pancreas. Round cells and rodlet cells are clustered between the gut and pancreas and the ventral body wall (cross section S10).
Male. There is a granuloma between the testis and the body wall. Acid fast negative. Eosinophilic round cell accumulation between the gut and the ventrolateral body wall. There are dermis lined invaginations in the lateral body wall. The invaginations are bilateral but more pronounced on one side. Possible atrophy of the underlying muscle at the site of invagination.
Male. Chronic inflammation with granulomas surrounds the swim bladder and extends into mesentery. Pooled blood with bubbles between kidney and swim bladder. There is a focal area of hemorrhage between the dermis and muscle on one side of the fish at the level of the swim bladder. One side of the dermis is thickened and invaginates into the inflamed tissue dorsal to the testis extending all the way to the contra lateral dermis (cross section S10 and S13). Acid fast negative.
Bact_Culture:
Renal culture; no growth on blood agar or Middlebrook 7H10.
Renal culture. Day 6 There are 2 non hemolytic colonies on the blood agar plate. Colonies are on the streak line in the 1st quadrant. They are white and appear dry and crystalline. OVDL biochemical assays confirmed a Mycobacterium. qPCR panel was positive for M. chelonae.
Renal culture; no growth on blood agar or Middlebrook 7H10.

Histopathology: Female.  Massive fibrotic lesion extending from kidney around spinal cord  through dorsal musculature and skin  posterior to dorsal fin. Multiple  large granulomas  coalescing granulomas occur throughout the chronic inflammation.  Adjacent muscle shows chronic myositis around the lesions.  PAS stained revealed pleomorphic fungal hyphae (apparently non septate) in many of the granulomas.  AF and Luna stains did where negative for mycobacteria and Pseudoloma  respectively.

Male. CNS multiple aggregates of Pseudoloma with associated moderate gliosis. Very large small cell carcinoma of intestine. Cells particularly small and dense (due to formalin fixation) extending through muscularis into serosa.
Male. Gill hyperplasia.

CaseDescr_right: Three zebrafish were submitted for histopathology.
Histopathology:
Male. As fish 1 prominent post mortem autolysis. Lesions consistent with severe mycobacteriosis with numerous granulomas in kidney coelom and heart. Also severe chronic pericariditis. Numerous acid fast bacilli are present within the granulomas consistent with mycobacteriosis. Some granulomas also contain P. neurophilia spores.
Male. Significant post mortem autolysis compromised interpretations of fine details. CNS: one large Pseudoloma aggregate. Muscle. 2 foci of inflammation and possible necrosis close to skin in ventral posterior region near anus. Although post mortem autolysis compromised the sections there was no evidence of granulomas (see Fish 2) Pseudocapillaria intestinal neoplasia or promiment gill hyperplasia.
Male. Gills: severe diffuse necrosis. Perhaps a perimortem agonal change. No other lesions. Internal organs showed no evidence of post mortem autolysis.
Fish_Entry_1: Male.  As fish 1  prominent post mortem autolysis.  Lesions consistent with severe mycobacteriosis  with numerous granulomas in kidney  coelom and heart. Also  severe chronic pericariditis.  Numerous acid fast bacilli are present within the granulomas  consistent with mycobacteriosis.  Some granulomas also contain P. neurophilia spores.
Fish_Entry_2: Male.  Significant post mortem autolysis compromised interpretations of fine details. CNS: one  large Pseudoloma aggregate. Muscle. 2 foci of inflammation and possible necrosis close to skin in ventral posterior region near anus.  Although post mortem autolysis compromised the sections  there was no evidence of granulomas (see Fish 2)  Pseudocapillaria  intestinal neoplasia or promiment gill hyperplasia.
Fish_Entry_3: Male.  Gills: severe  diffuse necrosis. Perhaps a perimortem agonal change.  No other lesions.  Internal organs showed no evidence of post mortem autolysis.

CaseDescr_left: Fourteen zebrafish were submitted for histopathology.  Fish look generally healthy, but some develop hemorrhages and/or skin lesions.  There have been some overcrowded tanks, which correlated with incidence.  Fish with hemorrhages were isolated, fed the normal diet, and showed now unusual behavior.
CaseDescr_right: Fourteen zebrafish were submitted for histopathology.  Fish look generally healthy, but some develop hemorrhages and/or skin lesions.  There have been some overcrowded tanks, which correlated with incidence.  Fish with hemorrhages were isolated, fed the normal diet, and showed now unusual behavior.
Histopathology:
Male. Very enlarged testis. Hypertrophy vs Spermacytic seminoma. Other than size histological morphology is normal
Male. Mutiple granulomas consistent with mycobacteriosis observed in kidney. Granulomas consistent with M. chelonae type with thin wall of epitheliod macropahges and large necrotic centers. / /CNS: Modterate multifocal menixitis at ventral aspects of spinal cord. Many Pseudoloma spores observed in the lesions and some lesions extend into the kidney. Recommend both Acid Fast and Luna as granulomas may be due to Pseudoloma Acid Fast and Luna revealed Pseudoloma spores in granuloma no mycobacteria
female. Ovary moderate EAIF with raft of eosinophilic debris and inflammation in posterior 1 3 of ovary.
Female. Intestine. Similar to some of the other fish with diffuse chronic inflammation of lamina propria. In this case the overlying epithelium exhibits promiment diffuse hyperplasia. CNS 1 aggregate of Pseudoloma in spinal cord with mild menixitis.
Female very similar to fish 8 with moderate EAIF and raft of debris in posterior ovary
Male. Similar to fish 2. Very enlarged spleen consistent with mylodysplastic syndrome. Intestine: prominent diffuse chronic inflammation in lamina propropria with increase in leucocytes in epithelium
Male. Very enlarged spleen consistent with mylodysplastic syndrome. Intestine: prominent diffuse chronic inflammation in lamina propropria with increase in leucocytes in epithelium
Male. Muscle two regions of chronic myositis. One focus posterior of coelomic cavity and a large region of severe chronic myositis with muscle debris in macrophages occupying the caudal peduncle region. Pseudoloma spores observed in lesions. Interesting no aggregates seen in CNS
Male. Kyphosis hump back and dysplastic vertebrae at vertebrae 14 17.
Male. Intestine: Moderate chronic inflammation of lamina propria particularly at proximal end. Overlying epithelium exhibits moderate hyperplasia and increase in leucocytes.
Female. Intestine moderate diffuse chronic inflammation of lamina propria. Epithelium shows significant increase in leucocytes.
Male: Testis: very enlarged hypertrophy vs spermacytic seminoma / /CNS: multiple regions of gliosis no microsporidia spores observed. Recommend Luna. No spores observed in gliosis lesion
Male. CNS: prominent chronic gliosis. Eight aggregates of Pseudoloma observed. Also moderate multifocal menixitis.

Histopathology: Male.  In the liver and pancreas there are foci of gold brown material.  In some cases the material appears to be in ductular structures (contained within squamous epithelial cells)  but in other areas hepatocytes appear to be full of the material. Male. Epitheliotrophic lymphosarcoma. Focused in gill chamber perhaps thymic region. Extending through epithelium of gill chamber orbit of eye and dermis in anterior region. Recommend Acid Fast and PAS.  RESULTS   Swim bladder lesion   numerous AF positive bacteria resent. Mycobacteriosis.  PAS revealed no fungi  but bacteria were slight PAS positive
Fish_Entry_16: Female.  Multiple  coalescing granulomas suggestive of mycobacteriosis.  Recommend acid fast (AF) stain.  AF Results:  numerous  small bacilli associated with lesions  but bacteria were clearly AF negative.
Fish_Entry_17: Female. Intestine: posterior  moderate dyplasia of epithelium  opposing serosa  was severe  diffuse  chronic inflammation

CaseDescr_left: Two zebrafish were submitted for histopathology.
CaseDescr_right: Two zebrafish were submitted for histopathology.
Histopathology:
Female. There is a large island of eosinophilic debris in the ovary with inflammation at the edges. Acid fast negative. The lamina propria is diffusely proliferative and changes extend through all layers to the serosa consistent with intestinal neoplasia. An aggregate of P. neurophilia spores is present in the spinal cord. Mike: Intestine adenocarcinoma with invasion into serosa. Neoplasia tumor
Female. Only immature eggs in the ovary. Mild diffuse myodegeneration in the tail muscles. Increased nuclear cytoplasm ratio in hepatocytes. These changes are consistent with inanition starvation. Multiple aggregates of Pseudoloma neurophilia spores are present in the hindbrain. Multiple granulomas containing brown gold pigment occur in the coelom and ovary. Acid fast pending. / /There is mild diffuse thickening proliferation in the lamina propria of the intestine. There is a large bubble in the blood surrounding the heart. This may be a post mortem artifact of specimen preparation when the body cavity was opened. Bubbles are not observed within vessels in sections examined. / /Mike: I agree Starvation syndrome. Intestine: Also flattened intestinal plates mild enteritis lamina propria with dysplasia with over laying epithelium. Bubble I agree not enough to call supersat. Acid fast bacilli in the granulomas; mycobacteriosis.

Kidney and Spleen: 160; The kidney is 3X normal size and contains abundant lymphoid blast cells. 160; These neoplastic lymphoid cells are also present throughout the spleen. 160; Morphologic Diagnosis: Kidney and Spleen: lymphosarcoma/ /Comment: 160; this case of lymphosarcoma is somewhat unusual for zebrafish. 160; Typically the lymphosarcoma in zebrafish is either thymic or multicentric (disseminated) with neoplastic lymphocytes throughout many organs including liver intestine and brain as well as kidney and spleen. 160; However as we look at more mutant lines of zebrafish we are seeing more lymphomyeloid neoplasms that do not fit the original dogma for wild type lines. 160; I recently diagnosed a lymphosarcoma that was identified in a transgenic fish due to bilateral exophthalmos. 160; Huge masses obliterated the eyes and the mass was also in the kidney but not elsewhere. 160; Without specific immunohistochemical or molecular markers the precise lineage of this neoplasm is difficult to identify definitively.

Acid fast positive bacilli are identified consistent with mycobacteriosis.
Fish_Entry_2: Female.  Moderate hepatic megalocytosis.  There is a large spindle cell tumor in the dorsal skeletal muscle  underlying spinal cord and vertebrae.  Nerve sheath tumor
Fish_Entry_4: Mike:  Yes
Fish_Entry_6: Jan: D08 24 F5
Fish_Entry_8: 1. Skeletal muscle:  160; a large  highly cellular mass is present in the skeletal muscle of the anterior trunk and has invaded extensively around the spine and spinal cord.  160; The mass is comprised of interlacing bundles of spindloid cells with pleomorphic ovoid to cigar shaped nuclei with moderate amounts of fibrillar eosinophilic cytoplasm.  160; Nuclei in the mass have coarsely granular chromatin and frequent mitoses.  160; Morphologic Diagnosis:  160; skeletal muscle  anterior trunk: leiomyosarcoma.
Fish_Entry_10: Comment:  160; Although we commonly see leiomyosarcoma in the gut of carcinogen treated zebrafish  it is rare to see this histologic type of neoplasm in the skeletal muscle of zebrafish.
Fish_Entry_12: Comment: a variety of diet and husbandry factors have been associated with hepatocyte megalocytosis.  160; If this is not a carcinogen treated fish  you may want to discuss diet and husbandry protocols to try to reduce toxicant exposure in this colony.  160; If this is a mutant line  then hepatocyte megalocytosis may occur due to genomic instability or other defects in the mitotic apparatus or cytokinesis mechanisms.
Fish_Entry_13: Female.  Dorsal section.  Severe right ocular dilation and edema.
Fish_Entry_14: Female.  Mild  locally extensive myositis and myodegeneration in the dorsal skeletal muscle.
Fish_Entry_16: Mike;  Unlike typical Pseudoloma myositis  this lesions appears to have a lot of myodegeneration with relatively little corresponding chonic myositis
Fish_Entry_17: Female.  Dorsal section.  Severe  diffuse  chronic  granulomatous inflammation permeates the peritoneal cavity  as a result of a deep ulcer in the lateral body wall.  Inflammatory tissue fills the caudal half of the peritoneal cavity  extending into the ovary and surrounding skeletal mucsle.  Acid fast positive bacilli are observed throughout the lesions  consistent with mycobacteriosis.
Fish_Entry_19: Mike: I agree.  This tank should be tag   8220;myco positive  8221;  Fish from this tank should be closely watched for morbidity.  If more myco occurs  we should send fish up to OSU for ID of bacterial species.
Fish_Entry_20: Female.  Moderate egg associated inflammation with a large amount of eosinophilic debris.  There is an area of fibroplasia and inflammation betweeen the caudal kidney and overlaying vertebrae.  There is a large focus of mild myositis and myodegeneration in the adjacent skeletal muscle.  Acid fast negative.
Fish_Entry_22: Mike: I agree   focal fibroplasia ventral to vertebrae  extending into kidney.  Focal myodegeneration with mild  chonic inflammation.  No microsporidia seen in macrophages
Fish_Entry_25: Female.  A large tumor occupies most of the peritoneal cavity.  Neoplastic cells invade surrounding skeletal muscle and ovary.  The renal interstitium is highly proliferative.  The mass contains areas of pallisading cells and areas with tubules.  Nephroblastoma
Fish_Entry_28: Mike:  Malignant nerve sheath tumor spindle cell sarcoma.  Kideny:  prominent interstitial hyperplasia.  I don  8217;t think this is neoplastic as more of a mixed population of hematopoietic cells.
Fish_Entry_32: 1. Abdomen:  160; a large  highly cellular neoplasm fills the caudal abdomen pushing viscera anteriorly.  160; The mass has infiltrated the ovary  kidney and skeletal muscle of the caudal trunk.  160; The mass forms sheets and papillary fronds throughout the abdomen.  160; The mass is comprised of pleomorphic spindloid  stellate to round cells with scant fibrillar cytoplasm.  160; In the mass are scattered tumor giant cells with marked karyomegaly.  160; Multifocal areas of necrosis are present in the mass.  160; Morphologic Diagnosis: Abdomen: Spindle cell sarcoma
Fish_Entry_33: 2. Ultimobranchial gland:  160; the ultimobranchial gland is 50X normal size and is composed of cluster and cords of polygonal neuroendocrine cells set in a fine fibrovascular stroma.  160; The normal acinar structure with acini lined by tall columnar cells with basally located nuclei is lost in this gland.  160; Morphologic diagnosis:  160; Ultimobranchial gland: adenoma
Fish_Entry_34: 3. Kidney and Spleen:  160; The kidney is 3X normal size and contains abundant lymphoid blast cells.  160; These neoplastic lymphoid cells are also present throughout the spleen.  160; Morphologic Diagnosis: Kidney and Spleen: lymphosarcoma
Fish_Entry_35: Comment:  160; this case of lymphosarcoma is somewhat unusual for zebrafish.  160; Typically the lymphosarcoma in zebrafish is either thymic or multicentric (disseminated) with neoplastic lymphocytes throughout many organs including liver  intestine and brain  as well as kidney and spleen.  160; However  as we look at more mutant lines of zebrafish we are seeing more lymphomyeloid neoplasms that do not fit the original dogma for wild type lines.  160; I recently diagnosed a lymphosarcoma that was identified in a transgenic fish due to bilateral exophthalmos.  160; Huge masses obliterated the eyes and the mass was also in the kidney  but not elsewhere.  160; Without specific immunohistochemical or molecular markers  the precise lineage of this neoplasm is difficult to identify definitively.

Fish_Entry_38: Mike:  Opercular lesion   focal epithelial hyperplaia  with prolferation extending into underlying dermis.
Fish_Entry_39: Male.  Curled operculae.  There is a small mass of basophilic cells at the tip of one of the operculae.

CaseDescr_left: Two zebrafish were submitted for histopathology.
CaseDescr_right: Two zebrafish were submitted for histopathology.
Histopathology:
Male. A spermatocytic seminoma occupies approximately one third of the coelomic cavity. Moderate chronic inflammation is present throughout the coelomic lining and mesenteric adipose tissue where it extends into pancreas. There is a large focus of granulomatous inflammation and necrosis in the liver. The borders of the granuloma are compromised by concomitant autolytic changes. Acid fast stain highlights numerous bacterial rods in the lesion and adjacent ducts. Acid fast negative./ /Throughout the liver parenchyma hepatocytes with enlarged nucear and cytoplasmic components are observed; mild diffuse hepatic megalocytosis.
Female. Mild to moderate kyphosis (dorsal curvature of the spine). Few megalocytic cells are noted in the liver; very mild hepatic megalocytosis. A few renal tubules are dilated and contain basophilic debris. One tubule in the rostral kidney is markedly dilated with a thickened wall and may contain bacteria. There is a focal are of degenerating egg material and chronic inflammation in the caudodorsal ovary. Acid fast negative.

Histopathology: Male.  Tissue surrounding the swim bladder is chronically inflamed.  Multiple large granulomas are present (S3).  Inflammation extends to the lateral body wall where no or very thin muscle occurs between the inflammation and the body wall (S6).  This occurs bilaterally and is prominent at the level of the pelvic fins (S9).  Inflammation extends into the caudoventral coelom  around the testis and into adjacent musculature to the more ventral body wall (S12).  The interior body wall appears  bilaterally compressed  pulled toward the midline (S15).  Cross sections of control fish are needed to assess whether or not this compression is normal and whether there is modegeneration in the body wall or these are normally thin areas of the body wall.  Inflammation with granulomas continues to extend to the ventral body wall at the vent (S18).  The lesion is mostly resolved in S24  and resolved in S27.  Acid fast negative (S4).  Granulomas contain PAS positive material including probable hyphae structures  consistent with fungal coelomitis.
